{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idcc6948fb-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s47530"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"47530"},"text":"§ 47530.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Nonapplication of sections 47528(a)–(d) and 47529 to aircraft outside the 48 contiguous States","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Sections 47528(a)–(d) and 47529 of this title do not apply to aircraft used only to provide air transportation outside the 48 contiguous States. A civil subsonic turbojet aircraft with a maximum weight of more than 75,000 pounds that is imported into a noncontiguous State or a territory or possession of the United States after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1990-11-04"},"text":"November 4, 1990","children":[],"tail":", may be used to provide air transportation in the 48 contiguous States only if the aircraft complies with the stage 3 noise levels."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idcc6948fc-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/272/s1/e"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–272, § 1(e)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-07-05"},"text":"July 5, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/1293"},"text":"108 Stat. 1293","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idcc6948fd-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"idcc6948fe-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:table","attrib":{"width":"50%","id":"idcc6948ff-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:colgroup","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"